verses.verse: Make a joyful shout <WH7321> to God, <WH430> all the earth! <WH776>
Sing to <WH2167> the glory <WH3519> of his name! <WH8034> Offer <WH7760> glory <WH3519> and praise! <WH8416>
Tell <WH559> God, <WH430> "How awesome <WH3372> are your deeds! <WH4639> Through the greatness <WH7230> of your power, <WH5797> your enemies <WH341> submit themselves to you. <WH3584>
All the earth <WH776> will worship <WH7812> you, <WH2167> and will sing to you; <WH2167> they will sing to your name. <WH8034>" Selah. <WH5542>
Come, <WH3212> and see <WH7200> God <WH430>'s deeds <WH4659>â€” awesome <WH3372> work <WH4659> on behalf of the children <WH1121> of men. <WH120>
He turned <WH2015> the sea <WH3220> into dry <WH3004> land. <WH5674> They went through the river <WH5104> on foot. <WH7272> There, <WH8055> we rejoiced in him.
He rules <WH4910> by his might <WH1369> forever. <WH5769> His eyes <WH5869> watch <WH6822> the nations. <WH1471> Don't <WH5637> let the rebellious rise up <WH7311> against him. <WH5542> Selah.
Praise <WH1288> our God, <WH430> you peoples! <WH5971> Make the sound <WH6963> of his praise <WH8416> heard, <WH8085>
who preserves <WH7760> our life <WH5315> among the living, <WH2416> and doesn't <WH5414> allow our feet <WH7272> to be moved. <WH4132>
For you, <WH430> God, have tested <WH974> us. <WH6884> You have refined us, <WH3701> as silver is refined. <WH6884>
You brought <WH935> us into prison. <WH4686> You laid <WH7760> a burden <WH4157> on our backs. <WH4975>
You allowed men <WH582> to ride <WH7392> over our heads. <WH7218> We went <WH935> through fire <WH784> and through water, <WH4325> but you brought us to <WH3318> the place of abundance. <WH7310>
I will come <WH935> into your temple <WH1004> with burnt offerings. <WH5930> I will pay <WH7999> my vows to you, <WH5088>
which my lips <WH8193> promised, <WH6475> and my mouth <WH6310> spoke, <WH6475> when I was in distress. <WH6862>
I will offer <WH5927> to you burnt offerings <WH5930> of fat animals, <WH4220> with the offering <WH7004> of rams, <WH352> I will offer <WH6213> bulls <WH1241> with goats. <WH6260> Selah. <WH5542>
Come, <WH3212> and hear, <WH8085> all you who fear <WH3373> God. <WH430> I will declare <WH5608> what he has done <WH6213> for my soul. <WH5315>
I cried <WH7121> to him with my mouth. <WH6310> He was extolled <WH7311> with <WH8478> my tongue. <WH3956>
If I cherished sin in my heart, <WH3820> the Lord wouldn't <WH136> have listened.
But most certainly, <WH403> God <WH430> has listened. <WH8085> He has heard <WH8085> the voice <WH6963> of my prayer. <WH8605>
Blessed <WH1288> be God, <WH430> who has not turned away <WH5493> my prayer, <WH8605> nor his loving kindness from me. <WH2617>
